%% Scania — OMS post-order FMAT notifications (2 async, fire-and-forget). Grounded in research-docs.md §12 OMS.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Sales as Zed Sales (order placed)
    participant OMS as OMS State Machine
    participant Cron as Zed Cron (queue worker)
    participant Cmd1 as OMS Command:<br/>Order-Created Notify
    participant Cmd2 as OMS Command:<br/>Payment+Activation Notify (Future)
    participant Client as FMAT Client
    participant FMAT as FMAT

    Note over Sales,FMAT: Fire-and-forget: transition <event> omitted → Zed drives the model via cron,<br/>caller not blocked. Command failure keeps item in source state (safe retry).
    Sales->>OMS: Order enters initial state
    OMS->>OMS: Transition (onEnter) → "notify FMAT: order created"
    OMS->>Cron: Schedule non-blocking transition
    Cron->>Cmd1: execute()
    Cmd1->>Client: POST order-created payload
    Client->>FMAT: POST /orders (REST, async) [Post-Order #1 — POC]
    alt FMAT accepts
        FMAT-->>Client: 2xx
        Client-->>Cmd1: OK
        Cmd1-->>OMS: Move to next state
    else FMAT error
        FMAT-->>Client: error
        Client-->>Cmd1: Exception
        Note right of Cmd1: Item stays in source state → retried on next cron run
    end

    rect rgb(149, 165, 166)
        Note over Cmd2,FMAT: Future scope — second notification
        OMS->>Cron: Transition → "notify FMAT: payment + activation date"
        Cron->>Cmd2: execute()
        Cmd2->>Client: POST payment + activation date
        Client->>FMAT: POST /orders/{id}/activation (REST, async) [Post-Order #2 — Future]
    end
